ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Great class in you are at all interested in IO.
I would recommend this course for anyone interested in learning about applied/empirical methodologies.
Yes, I learned that IO is applicable to lots of fields in economics!

This is a first course in empirical IO. The course discusses many crucial contributions in the field and mainly focuses on static analysis, emphasizing supply and demand estimation and empirical auctions. This course is crucial for understanding and applying modern IO techniques.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: don't think i want to do IO, but i definitely learned some tools from IO that can be useful in other fields
The course showed new empirical methods and identification strategies, I read a lot of relevant literature and got a broad overview of important contributions in the field.
